NETLI_MULTIROUTEONUDPON_RADIO.message: Give me the best media experience: This option allows Chrome to explore all possible network paths to find the best way to send and receive media, which may be different from normal web traffic.

NETLI_MULTIROUTEOFFUDPON_RADIO.message: Use only my default IP address: This option forces Chrome to use the same network path for media as normal web traffic, unless a proxy is present. To prevent performance degradation, media can be sent over UDP which will not be through proxies.

NETLI_MULTIROUTEOFFUDPOFF_RADIO.message: Use my proxy server (if present): This option forces Chrome to use the same network path for media as normal web traffic, in all cases. If a proxy is present, media will be forced through the proxy, using the TCP protocol. This will typically hurt media performance and increase the load on the proxy.

NETLI_MULTIROUTEOFFUDPOFF_NOT_SUPPORTED_.message: This option is not available before Chrome version 47.

NETLI_APPDESC.message: Configures how WebRTC's network traffic is routed by changing Chrome's privacy settings.
